The paper deals with supervised dimensionality reduction and manifold learning, which are topics that are commonly studied in the machine learning community. The use of nonlinear embeddings and smooth interpolators also suggests a focus on optimization and function approximation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks and regularization techniques also suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Systems and Control).
